## Design Decisions (2026-04-10)

1. **Binding check stays at auth level** — must gate everything under `[slug]`. If GitHub org is removed/revoked, everything halts immediately.
2. **Bind only for now** — no multi-step onboarding. Just GitHub bind.
3. **Binding is mandatory** — cannot be skipped. No org feature works without active binding.
4. **Efficient querying** — TeamSwitcher binding data should use best practices (batch query, shared cache).

## Solution Architecture

### Conditional Layout Rendering (No Redirect, No Loop)

The `[slug]/layout.tsx` checks binding and renders a **different shell** instead of redirecting:

```typescript
// (org)/[slug]/layout.tsx
export default async function OrgLayout({ children, params }) {
  const { slug } = await params;

  let org: OrgWithAccess["org"];
  try {
    const access = await requireOrgAccess(slug);
    org = access.org;
  } catch {
    notFound();
  }

  const binding = await getGitHubBinding(org.id);

  // Unbound → render setup shell (no sidebar, no workspace)
  if (!binding || binding.status !== "active") {
    return (
      <HydrateClient>
        <GitHubBindStep slug={slug} orgName={org.name} />
      </HydrateClient>
    );
  }

  // Bound → full workspace
  return (
    <HydrateClient>
      <OrgPageErrorBoundary orgSlug={slug}>
        <SidebarProvider>
          <AppSidebar />
          <CommandPalette />
          <div>
            <AppHeader />
            <SidebarInset>{children}</SidebarInset>
          </div>
        </SidebarProvider>
      </OrgPageErrorBoundary>
    </HydrateClient>
  );
}
```

**Why this works:**
- Binding check is at `[slug]` level — gates everything
- No redirect loop — layout renders different UI based on state
- Bind UI inherits full org context (`org.name`, `slug`) from `requireOrgAccess` — no `?slug=` query param needed
- URL is `/{slug}` — clean
- If binding revoked, everything halts on next load
- Future steps (invite) can extend the setup shell without new routes

### New Flow

```
/account/teams/new              (user)(pending-allowed) — create team, setActive()
  ↓ redirect to /{slug}
/{slug}                         (org)/[slug] — layout detects no binding → renders GitHubBindStep
  ↓ OAuth popup → onSuccess → page reload
/{slug}                         (org)/[slug] — layout detects active binding → renders workspace
```

**Key change**: `team-name-form.tsx` onSuccess redirects to `/${data.slug}` instead of `/account/teams/new/bind?slug=...`. The org layout handles the rest.

### Delete

- `apps/app/src/app/(app)/(user)/(pending-allowed)/account/teams/new/bind/` — entire directory, no longer needed

### TeamSwitcher Binding Badge — Efficient Query

#### Extend `listUserOrganizations` with batch DB join

`listUserOrganizations` (`api/app/src/router/user/organization.ts:24-47`) is currently pure Clerk API — returns `{ id, slug, name, role, imageUrl }[]`. Add one DB query:

```typescript
// After fetching Clerk memberships, batch-query binding status
const orgIds = memberships.map(m => m.organization.id);
const bindings = await db
  .select({
    clerkOrgId: githubOrgBindings.clerkOrgId,
    status: githubOrgBindings.status,
  })
  .from(githubOrgBindings)
  .where(inArray(githubOrgBindings.clerkOrgId, orgIds));

const bindingMap = new Map(bindings.map(b => [b.clerkOrgId, b.status]));

// Merge into response
return memberships.map(m => ({
  id: m.organization.id,
  slug: m.organization.slug,
  name: m.organization.name,
  role: m.role,
  imageUrl: m.organization.imageUrl,
  githubBound: bindingMap.get(m.organization.id) === "active",
}));
```

**Efficiency:**
- Single `SELECT ... WHERE clerk_org_id IN (...)` — indexed on unique `clerk_org_id` column
- Co-located with existing Clerk call — one additional SQL query per cache miss
- Shared via React Query cache with existing 5-min `staleTime` — all consumers (`app-sidebar.tsx`, `user-page-header.tsx`, `use-active-org.ts`) get binding status for free
- No additional network requests from any consumer

#### TeamSwitcher UI change

Extend `Organization` type in `packages/ui/src/components/app-header/team-switcher.tsx`:

```typescript
interface Organization {
  id: string;
  name: string;
  slug: string | null;
  githubBound?: boolean; // new — undefined for backwards compat
}
```

In the dropdown, show an indicator for unbound orgs:
- Amber dot (matching existing `installed-sources.tsx` pattern at lines 237-244) next to org name
- Or a small `Badge variant="destructive"` with "Setup" text

